headline: What Can Stop Bullets and Help DuPont Stock?
summary: Shares of  DuPont  rose early Thursday, partly because of an upbeat call from Wall Street, and partly because of the company’s incredibly strong Kevlar fiber, used in bulletproof vests.  DuPont stock was up 1.5% at $74.07, while the  and  were up 0.6%.  Citi analyst Patrick Cunningham put a 90-day “catalyst watch” on DuPont stock, a designation used when a Citi analyst believes a stock will move up or down, soon.

headline: Citi names DuPont top chemicals pick, sees earnings support from electronics, FX
summary: Investing.com -- Citigroup named DuPont (NYSE:DD) its top pick among North American specialty chemical stocks given an expected stability in second-quarter results and support from foreign exchange gains and improved margin trends in electronics.
